      "writtenOn": "2020-09-25T00:23:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I spent some time on this and it looks like the answer is `action_foreach`, but that comes with some interesting limitations. It sets up a bunch of limitations about where your source and output files can live and requires paths to go through a \"{{source}}\" template. \n\nHow long do tests take to build for you? Do you think this change would actually allow them to parallelize? Invoking the Python script from scratch hundreds of times in a row will add on extra cost, so if this doesn\u0027t actually allow parallelization, I\u0027m worried I could solve these issues but the final result would still be a net loss. We might actually do better to go in the opposite direction, and allow `skslc` to take in multiple input files. I would bet that would blow the doors off this approach.",
